lvl 60 Wizard <br>
Officer of Cats in Hats - Drinal <br>
http://www.catsinhats.net</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucabottp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CabotTP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 10:53:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sirens Grotto good for walking in?</span><hr size=1> <br>
I don't know about running through nekkid... I have yet to find a path from CS to WW without hitting see invis horses, but I haven't looked all that hard.<br>
<br>
On my server you bring your own group to SG, and I've never seen more than 2 groups in there at once, other than ppl passing through to WW.  Abscord/Evacuate/Succor drop you near the WW zone, yes.  The spot where they drop, there are 2 non-KoS mobs at your feet.  There is also a KoS roamer who paths over the evac spot, and the other 2 mobs will assist him if he aggros.<br>
<br>
When you drop in you seem to be in a hallway with 2 directions to go (3 really but the other wont be obvious right away).  One is a long curved hall, the other direction short and ends in 90 degree turn.  The short path to the 90 degree turn is the zone-out to WW.  It only takes about 2 seconds to reach it, so even if the roamer aggros you'd have to have an unlucky streak of stuns to die before you reach zone. <p><BR>Cabot Coriolis of Tholuxe Paells<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelaurieldragonstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elauriel Dragonstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 4:44:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sirens Grotto good for walking in?</span><hr size=1> On the Innoruuk server, it is most effective to bring your own group to SG also.  Although lately, there have been so many people in the zone that I would not discount the possibility of getting a pick-up group.  There seems to be nowhere I can go hunt quietly and regularly LOL....I swear the whole server shows up in any 50+ zone I  try to go to....arrrggg<br>
<br>
<br>
